# Opti-Route Project Roadmap

## Sprint 1 – Setup & Exploration (Due 11/10)
**Goals:** Establish the foundation for the project and gather references.  
**Tasks:**
- [ ] Create GitHub repository under KSU-IS organization and add `README.md`
- [ ] Explore at least one existing Python route-planning repository for reference
- [ ] Draft `projectroadmap.md` summarizing findings and inspirations
- [ ] Complete Exercise 6 (short paper describing project idea, goals, and features)
- [ ] Ensure commits show in GitHub

**Deliverables:**
- GitHub repo with README and roadmap
- Exercise 6 document

---

## Sprint 2 – Core Functionality Implementation
**Goals:** Develop basic route calculation and user input system.  
**Tasks:**
- [ ] Implement input page for origin and destination
- [ ] Implement route type options: fastest, scenic, beginner-friendly, fuel-efficient
- [ ] Write code to calculate and compare route options (using Google Maps API or sample dataset)
- [ ] Test routes with at least two examples
- [ ] Update `README.md` with progress and screenshots (if available)

**Deliverables:**
- Working prototype that calculates routes based on user preferences
- Updated README.md

---

## Sprint 3 – User Interface & Enhancements
**Goals:** Add usability features and optional visualization.  
**Tasks:**
- [ ] Develop optional visual display of the route (map integration using `folium` or `matplotlib`)
- [ ] Display estimated travel times and directions clearly
- [ ] Ensure route calculations adapt to user preferences (safety, fun, efficiency)
- [ ] Test full program with multiple scenarios and debug any issues
- [ ] Finalize `README.md` with full description, goals achieved, and screenshots

**Deliverables:**
- Fully functional **Opti-Route** program
- Complete documentation with examples and screenshots
